# ============================================================
# PERMISSION CORE POLICY
# ============================================================

status: canonical
layer: policy
domain: permission
scope: permission.core
system: civilization-os
owner: Boss
prepared_by: Zero

## purpose
Defines policy constraints for permission.

## policy_rules
Permission policy constrains:
- who may grant or revoke permission
- how delegation works
- what permission detail may be disclosed
- when permission paths must be denied or escalated

## required_behavior
- grant/revoke scope must be explicit
- delegation scope must be explicit
- disclosure scope must be explicit
- denial behavior must be explicit

## disclosure_matrix
- public permission summary
- holder-scoped detail
- operator/reviewer detail
- historical permission detail
- denied output

## allowed_denied_matrix
- allow permission action only for valid scope
- allow disclosure only for allowed actors
- deny hidden widening through delegation
- deny disclosure beyond allowed scope

## escalation_rules
If permission basis,
grant/revoke scope,
delegation scope,
or disclosure scope is unclear,
the permission path must stop and escalate.

## review_checklist
- grant/revoke policy is explicit
- delegation policy is explicit
- disclosure matrix exists
- denial behavior is explicit
